Here's an updated `BaseRepository` class that includes a method to find by a dynamic field. This example uses Entity Framework Core.

```csharp
public abstract class BaseRepository<T> : IBaseRepository<T> where T : class
{
    protected readonly DbContext _context;
    protected readonly DbSet<T> _dbSet;

    public BaseRepository(DbContext context)
    {
        _context = context;
        _dbSet = _context.Set<T>();
    }

    public async Task<T> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _dbSet.FindAsync(id);
    }

    public async Task<T> GetByDynamicFieldAsync(string field, object value)
    {
        return await _dbSet.FirstOrDefaultAsync(e => GetPropertyInfo(e.GetType(), field).GetValue(e).Equals(value));
    }

    private PropertyInfo GetPropertyInfo(Type type, string propertyName)
    {
        return type.GetProperty(propertyName);
    }
}
```

In this example, the `GetByDynamicFieldAsync` method uses reflection to get the property info of the specified field and then uses the `Equals` method to compare the value.

